<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12027e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12027e">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12027e"> 27(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> a P P&apos;s heritage doubtful</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">H&eacute;ritage de pr&ecirc;tre, ne le portez pas au plus haut de la maison (1). <br><font color="green">[The inheritance of a priest, don&apos;t carry it to the top of your house]</font> <br>Note 1: Parce que les biens qui en proviennent, s&apos;ils ne retournent aux pauvres, qui, d&apos;apr&egrave;s l&apos;opinion g&eacute;n&eacute;rale, en sont dans l&apos;origine les l&eacute;gitimes propri&eacute;taires. Il est donc sage &agrave; l&apos;h&eacute;ritier d&apos;un pr&ecirc;tre de ne pas les placer trop avant dans la maison, et m&ecirc;me de les laisser pr&egrave;s de la porte, puisqu&apos;ils doivent sortir sans tarder. <br><font color="green">[Because nothing good will come of these goods if they are not given back to the poor who, according to general opinion, are the legitimate owners. It is therefore better for the beneficiary of a priest, not to place them too far in the house and even to put them close to the door, since they must be taken away without delay]</font> <small> L-F. Sauv&eacute, <a name="LFSP" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#LFSP"><cite title="source">Proverbes et dictons de la Basse-Bretagne</cite></a> (1878) 53</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c12010d" href="c12all.htm#c12010d">VI.C.12:010(d)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
